    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2003-12-08</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2004-07-20T17:04:27Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Vocational Opportunities and Instruction through Cooperative Education Act of 2003 - VOICE Act of 2003 - Authorizes the Secretary of Education to enter into a partnership with a qualified local educational agency to conduct a model school-to-work program.</p> <p>Requires such program to: (1) provide course credits to secondary school students who participate in work-based learning experiences in the public or private sector; and (2) ensure that such students are paid at least the minimum wage under the Fair Labor Standards Act of 1938 for such work.</p> <p>Requires participating students to have: (1) no criminal background; (2) a grade point average of 2.0 or higher; and (3) a satisfactory record of school attendance.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
